Git tutorial for me.

git init {it creates hidden git repositery in your current folder}

git add .  { note : git add . will add all the folders or files present in the selected folder}

git commit -m "first commit"  {it stores the changes commited in your local repository and -m is used to provide additional message}

git branch -M main  {it moves/renames a branch to main}

git remote add origin main "remote link"  {to add remote repository }

git push -u origin main   { to push the selected the local repo to the remote repo }

if says refs error 
(failed to push  some refs to)

do these ::

git pull origin (your-branch)

git pull --rebase origin (branch-namee)





Additionally :

for creating username and loggning in
 
git config --global user.name "Ritesh-22893"

git config --global user.email "riteshpokhrel73@gmail.com"


To check added credentials :

git config --list


for viewing current status in git 

use git status




on addition to these :

git remote -v

git remote show origin 

